    <article aria-labelledby="recipe-intro">
      <section id="recipe-intro">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          This hearty Italian dish brings together rich flavors and simple ingredients for a comforting classic.
          Perfect for family dinners or meal prep!
        </p>

        <figure>
          <img src="spaghetti-bolognese.jpg" alt="A bowl of spaghetti bolognese garnished with basil and parmesan" width="500" />
          <figcaption>Rich, meaty sauce over tender spaghetti noodles — a timeless favorite.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="timing-info">
        <h2 id="timing-info">Cooking Time</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Prep Time: <time datetime="PT15M">15 minutes</time></li>
          <li>Cook Time: <time datetime="PT45M">45 minutes</time></li>
          <li>Total Time: <time datetime="PT1H">1 hour</time></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="ingredients" aria-labelledby="ingredients-heading">
        <h2 id="ingredients-heading">Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>400g spaghetti</li>
          <li>500g ground beef</li>
          <li>1 onion, chopped</li>
          <li>2 garlic cloves, minced</li>
          <li>800g canned tomatoes</li>
          <li>2 tbsp tomato paste</li>
          <li>1 tsp dried oregano</li>
          <li>Fresh basil and grated parmesan (to serve)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="steps" aria-labelledby="steps-heading">
        <h2 id="steps-heading">Preparation Steps</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Cook the spaghetti according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.</li>
          <li>Sauté the onion and garlic in a large pan until softened.</li>
          <li>Add ground beef and cook until browned.</li>
          <li>Stir in tomato paste, canned tomatoes, and oregano. Simmer for 30 minutes.</li>
          <li>Serve sauce over spaghetti. Garnish with fresh basil and parmesan.</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="difficulty-section">
        <h2 id="difficulty-section">Difficulty</h2>
        <label for="difficulty-meter">Level:</label>
        <meter id="difficulty-meter" min="0" max="10" value="4">Moderate</meter>
      </section>

